  <front>
   <head>STANZAS WRITTEN AT THE TOMB OF SHAKSPEARE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">FAIRY minstrels, haste away,</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Here attune the pensive lay;</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Where these roses crown the sod,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Avonia's Bard awaits his God.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Though Avon's stream for ever flow,</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">So sweet a Bard it ne'er shall know;</l>
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Child of Nature, void of Art,</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">How he knew the human heart!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">When the magic shell he strung,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Echo, glad, responsive sung;</l>
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Whilst the cowslip's fairy train</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Lightly trod the daisy'd plain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">And still at fall of dewy night,</l>
     <l n="14" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">By the Moon's uncertain light,</l>
     <l n="15" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Whilst they move to airs divine,</l>
     <l n="16" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Round his tomb they sweetly twine.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
